import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', bins=10, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    ax.set_xlabel('Borough')
    ax.set_ylabel('Longitude')
    max_longitude_borough = data.loc[data['cx'].idxmax()]['name']
    max_longitude_value = data['cx'].max()
    ax.axhline(max_longitude_value, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Longitude: {max_longitude_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('Which borough has the highest longitude value?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy', hue='name', palette='tab20', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between longitude and latitude values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.legend(title='Borough', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
